Cut and core @apples{4%cups}.

Mound apples in a buttered #9 inch pie plate{}.

Sprinkle with @orange juice{1/4%cup}.

Combine @sugar{1%cup}, @all purpose flour{3/4%cup}, @ground cinnamon{1/2%teaspoon}, @ground nutmeg{1/4%teaspoon}, and @salt{dash}.

Cut in @butter{1/2%cup} until the mixture is crumbly.

Sprinkle over apples.

Bake at 375 degrees for ~{45%minutes} or until apples are tender and topping is crisp.

Serve warm with cream.